node.text: Guys thanks for sticking around things here seem to be normalizing on the platform after I experienced a pretty serious dip and likes and interactions for quite some time. A lot of you guys reached out to me and mentioned it that seems to be going well again for the time being and I just wanted to thank you guys for staying with us. Hope you have a great weekend.

node.text: Guys, given what I’m seeing given what I’m hearing from other conservative accounts given the full frontal attack by big tech on anyone who is a conservative this is where you need to go to stay in touch with me. Go to my website, click the link in my bio, and just send me your email that way whatever happens I have a way to let you know where I actually end up. It’s simple, it takes two seconds, you do t have to buy anything, but it will allow me a place to make sure that I can still get my incredible followers the Content that they’ve come here for in the ever increasingly likely event that I’m thrown off and totally deplatformed.

node.text:
Praying for the victims of this terrible tragedy and those who lost their lives and limbs fighting to keep us safe in the two decades afterwards.🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸 
One of the most amazing things I noticed after 911 that we could use a little bit of right now was a sense of unity. We were all Americans, people were friendlier even amidst the aggressive hustle and bustle in New York there was a courtesy, a thoughtfulness that existing for a long time afterwards that stemmed from the incredible tragedy. There was a love of country and pride in being an American that seems to have since faded. We need to bring that back.

node.text: Where is all the talk of authoritarian dictatorships? We heard it for five years and then it just magically disappeared. I wonder what changed? Because I don’t think that any president has ever overreached so badly and yet the media is silent. If Donald Trump woke up in the morning they called him a dictator but when you actually have people acting like a dictator they are fine as long as they are Democrats. Look at what’s going on elsewhere in the world look at Australia and you will see why we cannot give up on our freedoms and are rights.

node.text: We did it guys! Radical anti gun Lunatic David Chipman out! It was an honor to help defend the Second Amendment and make sure that this radical anti-gun lunatic and alleged racist never took control of the ATF and therefore your Second Amendment rights. Even the New York Times gave me credit, and I’m happy to get involved have these fights. These are fights we need to have because once you lose your rights they do not come back and if you’ve been watching around the world you realize that they’re coming for your freedoms. Thanks to senators @tomcottonar and @sentedcruz amongst others in this fight. Check out @fieldethosjournal where we don’t compromise on the second amendment unlike so many others in the outdoors.
